      "content": "the problem is there actually isn't any new data. the candidate just realized they need the support of the industry lobbyists to win the upcoming primary, so they're switching sides to secure the funding. if we tell the press it's \"new data\" and they dig and find out we're making up economic indicators to cover the pivot, it'll be a total scandal. should we still go with the \"data-driven\" angle if we know it's not true?",
